credit.credit-words: Yet He found me; I beheld Him Bleeding on th'accurs√®d tree, Heard Him pray, "Forgive them, Father!" Lord, Thy love at last hath conquered: And my wistful heart said faintly, "Some of self, and some of Thee!"
O the bitter shame and sorrow
Higher than the highest heavens, Deeper than the deepest sea,
Grant me now my supplication, "None of self, and all of Thee!"
